Website Rules for Paws in Time

Content Organization

- Place all photo galleries under content/photos/
- Use consistent front matter for all content:
  - title: Page/gallery title
  - date: Publication date
  - description: Brief description
  - tags: Relevant tags
  - categories: Content category
  - featured_image: Main image for the content

Image Guidelines

- Store original images in Cloudflare R2
- Use Cloudflare Images for optimization:
  - Maximum width: 2048px for full-size
  - Thumbnail size: 300x300px
  - Gallery preview: 800x600px
- Include alt text for all images
- Use descriptive filenames (e.g., "golden-retriever-playing-2024.jpg")
- Implement lazy loading for gallery images

Gallery Structure

- Organize galleries by:
  - Date
  - Event type
  - Pet category
- Include metadata:
  - Location
  - Photographer
  - Camera settings (if relevant)
  - Pet information

Performance Requirements

- Page load time < 3 seconds
- First Contentful Paint < 1.5s
- Largest Contentful Paint < 2.5s
- Cumulative Layout Shift < 0.1
- First Input Delay < 100ms

SEO Guidelines

- Implement proper meta descriptions
- Use semantic HTML structure
- Create descriptive URLs
- Include OpenGraph tags
- Implement JSON-LD structured data
- Create XML sitemap

Security Measures

- Enable Cloudflare security features:
  - WAF (Web Application Firewall)
  - Bot protection
  - DDoS mitigation
- Implement proper CSP headers
- Use HTTPS everywhere
- Enable privacy-focused analytics

Responsive Design Requirements

- Breakpoints:
  - Mobile: 320px - 480px
  - Tablet: 481px - 768px
  - Desktop: 769px - 1024px
  - Large Desktop: 1025px+
- Mobile-first approach
- Touch-friendly navigation
- Optimized gallery grid for each device

Content Guidelines

- High-quality, original photographs only
- Consistent photo styling
- Clear, engaging descriptions
- Proper attribution for all content
- Regular content updates (minimum monthly)

User Experience

- Clear navigation structure
- Fast image loading
- Intuitive gallery browsing
- Easy sharing functionality
- Search and filter capabilities
- Accessible contact information

Maintenance

- Weekly backups of content
- Monthly performance audits
- Regular security updates
- Content freshness reviews
- Analytics monitoring

Development Workflow

- Use feature branches for new content
- Test all changes locally first
- Optimize images before upload
- Review performance metrics
- Document all configuration changes

Analytics and Monitoring

- Track key metrics:
  - Page views
  - Time on site
  - Popular galleries
  - User flow
  - Device usage
- Monitor error rates
- Track performance metrics

Accessibility Standards

- WCAG 2.1 AA compliance
- Keyboard navigation
- Screen reader compatibility
- Sufficient color contrast
- Clear focus indicators
- Alternative text for all images 